lly reside in smaller mass, less\nluminous galaxies; the present data do not allow us to choose one over the\nother. More trustworthy stellar velocity dispersions and accurate black hole\nmass measurements are required for a firmer statement about the locus of NLS1s\non the M_BH-sigma plane.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Nov 2006 21:00:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 27 Mar 2007 14:24:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
